## 3. APP BOOTSTRAP AND AUTH GUARD

### Bootstrap sequence (AppState.init)
1. Restore persisted session from UserDefaults
2. Restore DUPR ID store, DUPR ratings store, DUPR history store
3. Sync current user DUPR data from those stores
4. Restore checked-in booking IDs, club news notification preference, pinned club IDs
5. Background Task starts:
   a. If already signed in ‚Üí `refreshSessionIfPossible(silent: true)`
   b. `refreshClubs()` (always, even signed-out ‚Äî clubs are public)
   c. If signed in: `loadProfileFromBackendIfAvailable()`, `loadNotificationPreferencesIfNeeded()`, `refreshBookings(silent: true)`, `refreshUpcomingGames()`
   d. Set `isInitialBootstrapComplete = true`

### Auth guard (RootView pattern ‚Äî NOT fullScreenCover)
```
authState != .signedOut && !isInitialBootstrapComplete && profile == nil
```
While this condition is true: show loading/splash screen.
NEVER use `fullScreenCover(isPresented: .constant(appState.isAuthenticating))` ‚Äî this fires on token refresh and overlays MainTabView.

### After sign-in: `postAuthenticationBootstrap()`
- `loadProfileFromBackendIfAvailable()` ‚Üí syncs Supabase ‚Üí UserDefaults DUPR
- `loadNotificationPreferencesIfNeeded()`
- `refreshBookings(silent: true)`
- `refreshUpcomingGames()`
- `refreshMemberships()`
- `registerRemotePushTokenIfNeeded()`
- `isInitialBootstrapComplete = true`

### On sign-out
- Push token cleared from server (PATCH profiles with nil APNs token) BEFORE wiping session
- All @Published state reset to empty
- All realtime club chat clients stopped
- All background tasks cancelled
- `dataProvider.setAccessToken(nil)` called

