## 4. MAIN TAB VIEW

### Tab order and icons
| Index | Tab | Label | Icon |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | Home | "Home" | `house.fill` |
| 1 | Clubs | "Clubs" | `building.2` |
| 2 | Bookings | "Bookings" | `calendar` |
| 3 | Notifications | "Notifications" | `bell` |
| 4 | Profile | "Profile" | `person.crop.circle` |

### Tab bar behaviour
- `tint`: `Brand.primaryText` (dark text, not a color accent)
- Style: `DefaultTabViewStyle()` ‚Äî MUST be set explicitly on iPad (iOS 18+ defaults to sidebar/top-bar without it)
- `toolbarBackground(.visible, for: .tabBar)` ‚Äî always opaque tab bar
- Notification tab shows badge: `appState.unreadNotificationCount` (hidden when 0)

### Deep link handling (MainTabView.handleDeepLink)
```
.club(id):
  1. Find club in appState.clubs (memory only ‚Äî no DB fallback)
  2. selectedTab = .clubs
  3. DispatchQueue.main.asyncAfter(0.1) ‚Üí set deepLinkClub (NavigationDestination on Clubs stack)
  4. pendingDeepLink = nil

.game(id):
  1. Search memory: gamesByClubID.values + bookings cache
  2. If found ‚Üí asyncAfter(0.1) ‚Üí set deepLinkGame (sheet presentation)
  3. If NOT found ‚Üí appState.resolveGame(id:) ‚Üí fetch from DB ‚Üí then set deepLinkGame
  4. pendingDeepLink = nil in both paths

.review:
  ‚Üí no-op (pendingDeepLink = nil only)
```
- Cold-launch deep link: `.task` checks `appState.pendingDeepLink` once on first appear because `onChange` won't fire for a value that was already set when the view first enters the hierarchy.
- NotificationCenter `.bookADinkOpenNotificationsTab` ‚Üí switches `selectedTab = .notifications`

### Navigation presentation styles
- Club detail: `navigationDestination(item: $deepLinkClub)` ‚Äî pushed within Clubs NavigationStack
- Game detail: `.sheet(item: $deepLinkGame)` ‚Äî presented as sheet from MainTabView level
- NotificationsView: owns its OWN `NavigationStack` so club taps push inline

