## 7. GAME DETAIL VIEW

*(Partial read from prior session ‚Äî key supplement here)*

### PaymentSheet result handling
```
.completed:
  ‚Üí if isDeferred (waitlist hold path):
       appState.confirmPendingBooking(bookingID:, stripePaymentIntentID:, platformFeeCents:,
                                       clubPayoutCents:, creditsAppliedCents:, clubID: game.clubID)
  ‚Üí else (new booking):
       appState.requestBooking(for: game, stripePaymentIntentID:, platformFeeCents:,
                               clubPayoutCents:, creditsAppliedCents:)

.canceled:
  ‚Üí clear all pending* state, no booking insert

.failed(error):
  ‚Üí clear all pending* state, set paymentErrorMessage
```

### Inline booked actions (shown when booking is confirmed)
- "Add to Calendar" / "Remove from Calendar" button (EKEventStore integration)
- "Set Reminder" / "Remove Reminder" button (UNUserNotificationCenter local push)
- Both buttons use `appState.scheduleStore` (separate @EnvironmentObject ‚Äî not AppState)
- Calendar export state: `appState.hasCalendarExport(for: game)`, `appState.isExportingCalendar(for: game)`
- Reminder state: `appState.hasReminder(for: game)`
- **Android v1 does NOT include calendar/reminder actions** ‚Äî these are platform-specific iOS features

### Computed properties critical for Android parity
- `isClubAdminUser`: `appState.isClubAdmin(for: game.clubID)` ‚Äî gates admin sections
- `canViewAttendees`: members + admins (not non-members); shown as locked icon + count otherwise
- `canBookGameByClubMembership`: must be approved/unknown member (or admin) to book
- `currentGame`: live-resolved game from `appState.gamesByClubID` ‚Äî NOT the init-injected `game` param (which may be stale)
- `spotsLeft`: `currentGame.maxPlayers - confirmedCount` (server count not local)
- `isGameFull`: `spotsLeft <= 0`
- `tagLine`: composite label from skill level, game type, duration

### Hold countdown (pending_payment state)
- Live timer: `GameDetailViewModel` (or @State Timer) updating every second
- Displays: "Complete Booking ¬∑ $X.XX" CTA with countdown "X:XX remaining"
- On hold expiry: CTA switches to "Spot hold expired" with "Refresh" button
- When user opens app AFTER expiry: shows expired state immediately (no countdown shown)

