## 10. CLUB CHAT (ClubNewsView)

### Composer
- `postText`: `@State` in `ClubNewsView` (NOT in AppState ‚Äî view-level only)
- `isAnnouncementPost`: toggle in ClubNewsView ‚Äî only shown when `isClubModerator == true`
- Announcement mode post ‚Üí different visual treatment (megaphone icon, distinct background)
- Draft images: `[DraftNewsImage]` ‚Äî `@State` in view; cleared on post
- Photo picker: `PhotosPickerItem` via SwiftUI `PhotosUI`
- Camera: UIImagePickerController wrapped as sheet (`showCamera`)
- Attachment options: sheet showing camera vs. photo library choice
- Mention candidates: `[ClubDirectoryMember]` ‚Äî populated as user types `@`

### Who can post
```
canPost:
  - isClubModerator ‚Üí always true
  - membershipState: .approved or .unknown ‚Üí true
  - .none, .pending, .rejected ‚Üí false (composer shown but disabled or hidden)
```

### Comment draft (CRITICAL ‚Äî do not lift)
- `commentDraft` lives as `@State private var commentDraft: String = ""` INSIDE `ClubNewsPostCard`
- Lifting to `ClubNewsView` or parent as `[UUID: String]` causes FULL re-render of ALL cards on every keystroke (keyboard lag)
- This is a known iOS production bug that was fixed by keeping state card-local
- Android: comment draft must be `remember { mutableStateOf("") }` inside the card Composable, NOT in the ViewModel

### Optimistic updates
- Like: increment `likeCount` on post locally, revert on failure
- Comment: increment `commentCount` locally, append comment, revert on failure
- Post: append to local list before server confirmation
- Do NOT call full `refreshClubNews` after every interaction

### Hidden posts
- `hiddenPostIDs: Set<UUID>` ‚Äî locally hidden by "hide" action (not a DB write in v1)
- Posts filtered: `posts = appState.clubNewsPosts(for: club).filter { !hiddenPostIDs.contains($0.id) }`

### Realtime / refresh
- Realtime clients per club: `clubChatRealtimeClients: [UUID: SupabaseClubChatRealtimeClient]`
- Started when club chat tab first opens; stopped on sign-out
- `scenePhase` change triggers refresh when app returns to foreground

### Push error banner
- `appState.remotePushRegistrationErrorMessage`: shown as error banner at top of chat view when non-nil

