## 14. LOCAL STATE / SWIFTUI BEHAVIOUR RISKS FOR ANDROID

These patterns exist in iOS and have caused bugs. Android must NOT repeat them.

| iOS Pattern | Risk | Android Rule |
|---|---|---|
| `commentDraft` lifted to parent as `[UUID: String]` | Full card list re-render on every keystroke | Keep as `remember { mutableStateOf("") }` inside card Composable |
| `fullScreenCover(isPresented: .constant(appState.isAuthenticating))` | Fires on token refresh; overlays MainTabView | Do NOT gate a fullScreenCover on the auth-loading boolean |
| `GameDetailView` reading `game.feeAmount` (injected param, possibly stale) | Credit balance loads against wrong fee | Always use `currentGame.feeAmount` (live-resolved from gamesByClubID) |
| `confirmPendingBooking` called without `clubID` | Credit deduction skipped; balance not updated | Always pass `clubID` ‚Äî it is required, not optional |
| Loading all club data on ClubDetailView open | Causes performance freeze on tab switch | Load on tab change only (lazy by selected tab) |
| Global `creditBalanceCents: Int` | Club-scoped credits collapse; multi-club users get wrong balance | Use `creditBalanceByClubId: Map<UUID, Int>` exclusively |
| UUID keys not lowercased in PostgREST filters | Returns 0 rows silently | Always `.lowercase()` before filter |
| `tournament` sent as skill_level | PostgreSQL enum error (22P02) | Map `.tournament` to `"advanced"` if it ever appears |

